<h2>Washington Incentives & Rebates</h2>
<p>Washington offers a comprehensive array of incentives that make solar and HVAC investments financially attractive for homeowners. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% credit against federal income taxes for solar installations through 2032, with the credit decreasing to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. This credit applies to the total system cost including equipment, installation, and associated electrical work, representing substantial savings for most installations.</p>

<p>The state's Renewable Energy Sales Tax Exemption eliminates sales tax on solar equipment purchases, providing immediate savings of 6.5% to 10.4% depending on local tax rates. This exemption applies to solar panels, inverters, mounting equipment, and other qualifying renewable energy components, but does not include installation labor. Additionally, Washington has eliminated the solar equipment use tax, ensuring no additional tax burden for solar installations.</p>

<p>Puget Sound Energy offers several programs benefiting both solar and HVAC upgrades. Their net metering program credits solar customers at retail rates for excess electricity fed back into the grid, maximizing the financial benefits of solar production. The utility's Energy Efficiency Programs provide rebates up to \$2,500 for qualifying heat pump installations and up to \$1,200 for high-efficiency ducted systems. PSE also offers low-interest financing options for energy efficiency improvements, making upfront costs more manageable for qualifying customers.</p>

<p>Local utility districts throughout Washington provide additional rebates and incentives. Seattle City Light offers rebates up to \$3,000 for air-source heat pumps and up to \$5,000 for geothermal systems. Tacoma Power provides similar incentives, while Snohomish PUD offers both rebates and favorable net metering terms for solar installations. Many utilities also provide free energy audits and additional rebates for comprehensive home efficiency improvements that combine multiple upgrades.</p>

