    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">How much do solar panels cost in Washington?</h3>
    <p>Solar panel costs in Washington typically range from \$15,000 to \$31,500 before incentives for systems sized between 5kW and 10kW. After applying the 30% federal tax credit and state sales tax exemption, homeowners can expect to pay \$10,500 to \$22,050 for installed systems. The cost per watt ranges from \$2.65 to \$3.15 before incentives, which aligns with national averages. Financing options through solar loans, leases, and power purchase agreements can reduce or eliminate upfront costs while still providing immediate savings on electricity bills.</p>
